title: A community lost, a movement born: International Hotel evictions still shaping S.F. 40 years later
description: The evictions and later destruction of the I-Hotel dispersed Manilatown's last residents, but the events linger in the minds of Filipino Americans today who are working to establish and protect a new cultural district South of Market.
seo_title: International Hotel development battle still shaping S.F. 40 years later
author: Brandon Yu, Lucio Villa
twitter_text: A community lost, a movement born: How International Hotel development battle is still shaping S.F. 40 years later.
